(1, 'What we have learned ', 'Learning project 1 ', '<h1> Hello <br> Over the past few weeks we have been introduced to many things </h1> \r\n<p> On our first week we looked at VS Code and how start to use HTML</p> \r\n<p> We Then used Mimo at home <br> to learn how to use HTML CSS and Javascript </p> \r\n<p> We then the next week downloaded GITHUB Desktop and Xampp which is the file server </p> \r\n<p> Then Next week we started creating a film site with trailors for Films in 2024 </p>', '', '2024-09-26');
INSERT INTO `posts` (`id`, `title`, `description`, `post_txt`, `picture`, `created`) VALUES
(2, 'Project 1 Evaluation ', 'Evaluating Project 1 ', '\r\nDuring this project, I have overcome many challenges to provide a decent website, which I believe is up to a good standard and does the basics of any blog site.\r\nI went into the project with no experience in HTML and CSS, it was completely new to me, but I was keen to learn a new programming language. I used apps like Mimo and was introduced to a website called w3 schools which both helped me with learning key HTML and CSS and also PHP , it is a very useful resource which I will be using in future projects it helped me a lot considering HTML , PHP and CSS is all new to me.   \r\n\r\n\r\nAs we went on, we practiced a basic film site and saved the step-by-step process into creating html.\r\nThen we created PHP scripts to start our blogsite with our tutor, he went through key things like Validation scripts and key forms.\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n \r\n, so, we could do the basics, create posts, list posts, retrieve post and delete posts. \r\n Stage 1\r\nWe then  we started our Requirements task for this project, We looked at the problem space Problem Space P1 , User and author persona  so I know what the user wants from my website. I used research to get a typical user persona of a website user. I considered many other methods like having a survey to generate an idea of enthusiastic people wanting to access a blog site. \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\nI had a deep analysis with my colleagues about stakeholders and their needs, we communicated and shared our ideas and had good teamwork, a good technique in any team which I could develop by teamwork skills especially in Project 3. We had to have so many branches to analyse the different people that would use their website and how we can apply it to them and the website should have a good user experience and accessibility. \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\nThe user acceptance criteria were another requirement before our next stage, the purpose.\r\nwas to establish ideas/needs from the user that should be in my website, \r\nI will later on evaluate if my final website will meet these scenarios.\r\nStage 2 \r\nThe User journey diagram was to establish a route for users and how they can access each page all from the home page itself,\r\nAs I designed my website for the home page to be a key area\r\nwhere multiple pages can be accessed either by the header or just buttons.\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\nAnother key process of the Research was to research. \r\nand analyse other websites for inspiration or research for bad examples,\r\nI had an in depth look at a website called forum the new fishy, which I picked out as a bed example. \r\nI wanted to have a better-quality design to the website, but the functionality of the fishy was good and I implemented. \r\nSome features like the log in and registered but in my opinion designed better.  \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\nA key process was to design a database schema for my website,\r\nthis would make my work more planned and a quicker less rushed output to code, the database is so key for the code it. \r\nwouldn\'t work without it So to have it organised and ready for use.\r\nis a good opportunity, to set up at home as well for more website testing. \r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\nAfter all that it was time to design my website, in my opinion I took way to long doing this especially it was hard to code. \r\nSo not all designs went in, it is a good principle to design before executing, but I took too long doing so, I created other 14 pages on Figma.\r\nOf possible designs, they were advanced and quite hard to execute while coding, \r\n\r\n\r\nStage 3 \r\nAfter nearly 3 weeks of designing my website, it was time to code with 2 weeks left, \r\nIt was tough to implement my design to as good of standard as I would have liked. \r\nOr designed for but I had to crack on and create a functional website as part of the project this.\r\nHas to be independent work, we built on from earlier scripts but independently developed them.  \r\n \r\nOverall, it was a tough experience, but I used the correct resources to rejig my brain ready for \r\nCoding the site and after a few tough weeks and a lot of files being created I was happy with the \r\nOutcome of my website, some things wasn\'t as planned from my designs, but I feel it was a consistent colour scheme. \r\nBetter than my designs, and I mainly focused on the functionality of the blogsite which I feel I did good in, \r\nThere are many pages that I didn\'t have the time to code but the majority in my opinion function and look professional. \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n \r\nAfter finishing my code, I asked for user feedback they said points like this.\r\n \r\n\"Home screen is solid and would be a 3 star\" -Euan. \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nOverall, the feedback is positive. \r\nFrom my final product of my website, I asked for some feedback from people with an un-biased opinion and someone who has not done web development before to ask for their opinion. \r\n \r\n<<Feedback.png>>\r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n \r\n \r\nJacob goes through positives of my website and negatives which I could fix / solve in future projects. \r\n \r\n \r\nFor my user acceptance criteria I feel I haven’t got everything I would of liked User Acceptance Criteria\r\nFirstly, I have not implemented in my code that I know a certain account is making that post, Users can upload pictures in their blog post which I believe was one of the harder features to implement into my code. \r\nReaders can see other people posts, my website is aesthetically pleasing the cs may not be complicated, but it is simple and is clear for the users. \r\nThe code enables posts to be sanitized, and personal data is as well, passwords are also hashed to avoid SQL injection attacks. \r\nAnother part of the UAC is that users can give feedback, a part I found quite easy to implement in my website, as my knowledge for PHP grew further. \r\n \r\nSoftware for website -\r\nDuring the process of creating the website I used different software to write and analyse code for my project\r\n \r\nFor me Dreamweaver has some good features like \r\n Live View editing: Dreamweaver offers a convenient feature where you can directly edit text and image attributes and add classes in the Live View. \r\nAlthough, in vs code live editing and preview will have to be done by enabling certain extensions. \r\nDreamweaver can also directly go to a server without using xammp although xampp could still be used if preferred. \r\n\r\n\r\nVS Code although requires software like xampp to run the live server (localhost) of the website. \r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\n \r\nFor a paid software I think dreamweaver has more advanced features and for experienced coders who are willing to spend money on it and wanted something from vs code I would recommend but for new coders I would recommend vs code, Vs code is simple and many extensions can be added if need and other programming languages can be accessed , vs code really isn’t overwhelming which I think dreamweaver is , I used vs code as a new coder for my website\r\nAnother positive feature of vs code is the access to git hub where you can push files to your account.\r\n \r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n \r\nTest case ID	Description	Status	Result	Error/notes\r\n1	Register Account	Pass	Account registered and inserted into database	 \r\n2	Logging In 	Pass	Account I registered was able to log in 	 \r\n3	Creating Post	Pass	User Created Post Successfully	 \r\n4	Adding photo to post	Pass	Picture was added and stored in database	 \r\n5	Search for post	Pass	Search worked and the post was able to come up	 \r\n6	Edit Post	Pass	Was able to edit post which validated to database	 \r\n7	Delete Post	Pass	Was able to delete post from database	 \r\n8	Create Feedback 	Pass	Sent feedback and was validated to database	 \r\n9	Click Icons	Pass	All icons on header worked and went to the correct location	 \r\n10	Click on images on home screen	Pass	The images on home screen went to the relevant post	 \r\n11	Buttons check	Pass	All buttons go to the right places and do the correct actions. 	 \r\n12	Account written in posts	skipped	All posts should have an account that wrote its post	Did not get on to setting it up\r\n13	Sanitised posts and safety	Pass	All posts are sanitised 	 \r\n \r\n \r\nThis is my test log for the website, in line with my user acceptance criteria, I was disappointed with features to an account and feel if I had better time management this would be improved. \r\n \r\n \r\nStage 4 \r\nStage 4 involved finalising files and making sure they are ready for finalisation in a ZIP folder. Also, it was a time to update my project planner from Stage 1 onwards. Stage 4 is also to reflect on my website and this project (what I am doing here) \r\n \r\n \r\nOverall, I am impressed with the final outcome of the website , considering I left it very late to finish of the coding I think my final outcome is a professional , easy to use website and for my first time creating a website it was a good attempt, they\'re some things in my approach to creating and creating the website that things that I would change , one main thing is the account system , also a feature where the website could be used on a smaller device as my website is heavily designed for a desktop/laptop. If I were to do the project again, they are many things I would do differently but as the project went on, I have learned more about website development, and I think this will set me up for many other projects. \r\n \r\nI have shown some good skills in the project like teamwork and communication, I asked for helps from my peers and tutor if I needed to, I also dished out help to my peers if needed. Another skill could be resilience which I have developed throughout the project, I was patient with my code as every code starts of poor and didn\'t give up if they were errors, I worked out the errors and was able to fix them instead of giving up on them.\r\nThey were a lot of problems and obstacles, but I was happy to solve them and feel proud of my final product that I will submit. \r\n \r\nI tried to put in the 8 Shneiderman\'s key principles into the website as I believe they should be in all websites and is the key to success and is professional. \r\n', , '2024-12-03');
